    <article xml:id="notes">
        <section xml:id="sec-field-extensions" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
            <title>Field extensions</title>
            <theorem xml:id="thm-iso-simple-field-extensions">
                <statement>
                    <p>
                        Suppose that <m>\sigma\colon F\to F'</m> is an isomorphism of fields. Let <m>p\in F[x]</m> be an irreducible polynomial and let <m>p'\in F'[x]</m> be a polynomial obtained from <m>p</m> by applying <m>\sigma</m> to coefficients of <m>p</m>. If <m>\alpha</m> (resp., <m>\beta</m>) is a root of <m>p</m> (resp., <m>p'</m>) in some field extension of <m>F</m> (resp., <m>F'</m>), then there is an isomorphism <m>\widetilde{\sigma}\colon F(\alpha)\to F'(\beta)</m>.
                    </p>
                </statement>
            </theorem>
            <proof>
                <p>
                    Note that <m>p'</m> is also irreducible. Indeed, <m>\sigma</m> induces an isomorphism of rings <m>F[x]\simeq F'[x]</m> by defining <m>\sum a_ix^i\mapsto\sum\sigma(a_i)x^i</m>. Furthermore, this isomorphism induces an isomorphism of <m>F[x]/(p)\xrightarrow{\sigma_x} F'[x]/(p')</m> given by <m>\sum a_ix^i+(p)\mapsto \sum\sigma(a_i)x^i+(p')</m>. In the following diagram, we can consider the isomorphism <m>\widetilde{\sigma}=\ev_\beta\circ\sigma_x\circ{\ev_\alpha}^{-1}</m>.
                </p>
               <figure>
          <caption></caption>
          <image width="50%">
          <latex-image>
            
\begin{tikzcd}
	F \amp {F[x]} \amp {F[x]/(p)} \amp {F(\alpha)} \\
	{F'} \amp {F'[x]} \amp {F'[x]/(p')} \amp {F'(\beta)}
	\arrow["i", from=1-1, to=1-2]
	\arrow["\sigma"', from=1-1, to=2-1]
	\arrow["{\pi_F}", from=1-2, to=1-3]
	\arrow[from=1-2, to=2-2]
	\arrow["{\ev_{\alpha}}", from=1-3, to=1-4]
	\arrow["{\sigma_x}"', from=1-3, to=2-3]
	\arrow["{\widetilde{\sigma}}", dashed, from=1-4, to=2-4]
	\arrow["{i'}"', from=2-1, to=2-2]
	\arrow["{\pi_{F'}}"', from=2-2, to=2-3]
	\arrow["{\ev_\beta}"', from=2-3, to=2-4]
\end{tikzcd}
          </latex-image>
          </image>
        </figure>
            </proof>
        </section>
    </article>
